STEP-1 Cluster Setup (Minikube)
You practiced:
minikube start
kubectl get nodes
kubectl cluster-info
You also handled segmentation fault issue and binary repair.
Missing Scenario (important)
Real engineers also verify cluster health.
Practice these:
kubectl get componentstatuses
kubectl get all -A
kubectl get pods -n kube-system
Why?
Because in real projects sometimes scheduler or controller fails.

STEP-2 kubectl basics
You practiced:
kubectl get nodes
kubectl get pods
kubectl apply
Missing scenarios
Learn these daily kubectl operations:
kubectl delete pod
kubectl edit deployment
kubectl explain deployment
kubectl get pods -o wide
Why?
DevOps engineers constantly modify resources live.
Example interview question:
How do you modify a running deployment?
Answer:
kubectl edit deployment myapp

STEP-3 Docker Image (onsapp)
You practiced:
docker build
docker tag
docker push
And pushed to Docker Hub.
Missing scenario
Rebuild and redeploy new version.
Example real scenario:
v1 → bug → rebuild → v2
Practice:
docker build -t hansyy/survey-app:v5 .
docker push hansyy/survey-app:v5
Then update deployment image.

STEP-4 Pod Deployment
You deployed:
pod.yaml
And handled:
ImagePullBackOff
CrashLoopBackOff
YAML syntax error
This is excellent learning.
Missing scenario
Pod restart behavior.
Practice:
kubectl delete pod survey-app-pod
Observe:
Pod will NOT restart automatically.
This teaches why pods should not be used directly in production.
This scenario is often asked in interviews.

STEP-5 Debugging
You practiced the 3 most important commands:
kubectl logs
kubectl exec
kubectl describe
And debugged:
DB error
missing driver
env variables
This is real production troubleshooting.
Missing scenarios
Two useful log options:
kubectl logs -f
kubectl logs --previous
These help when containers restart repeatedly.

STEP-6 Deployment (ReplicaSet)
You did:
replicas: 3
kubectl scale deployment
kubectl get pods
And tested pod auto recreation.
Excellent.
Missing scenario
Deployment self-healing.
Practice:
kubectl delete pod <pod-name>
Observe:
ReplicaSet creates new pod automatically.
This demonstrates high availability.

STEP-7 Rolling Updates
You covered:
kubectl rollout status
kubectl rollout history
kubectl rollout undo
Very good — many learners skip this.
Missing scenario
Deployment failure rollback.
Practice:
Update deployment with bad image.
Example:
image: hansyy/survey-app:wrongtag
Then observe:
kubectl rollout status deployment/survey-app-deployment
Then rollback:
kubectl rollout undo deployment/survey-app-deployment
This is very common in real production incidents.

STEP-8 Services
You learned:
ClusterIP
NodePort
And exposed the application.
You also learned selector mismatch problem — very important.
Missing scenarios
Two service debugging checks:
kubectl get endpoints
kubectl describe svc
Why?
Because sometimes service exists but no pods connected.

